text: Cabanatuan is a city in the province of Nueva Ecija, Philippines. According to the 2020 census, 327,325 people lived there, which makes it the largest city by population in Nueva Ecija. The city is known for being home to more than 30,000 motorized tricycles, which makes it the "Tricycle Capital of the Philippines". It is the main economic, educational, medical, entertainment, shopping, and transportation center in Nueva Ecija. Category:Cities in the Philippines Category:Nueva Ecija
title: Cabanatuan
